# Backend Reliability Rules

- Validate request payloads at route boundaries.
- Keep API response shapes stable and explicit.
- Return actionable error details without leaking secrets.
- Ensure selected LLM provider/model is preserved through execution path.
- Keep retries/timeouts bounded and logged.
- Never let observability failures break primary business flow.
- For config changes, test merge behavior with runtime overrides.
